Edit: If you want to use the value in response, you can directly use it in response like this: 

     @Bean
        public WebClient getWebClient() {
            return WebClient.builder().filter((request, next) -&gt; {
                String value = ThreadLocalContext.get(&quot;test-variable&quot;);
                LOGGER.info(&quot;Value = &quot; + value);
                return next.exchange(request)
                        .doOnNext(clientResponse -&gt; {
                            //You can modify this code to put all the values as a map from thread local
