This maybe because of different device sizes. The `TextView` is having the entire table but it is not showing due to smaller device screen. If you could scroll your screen you would be able to see the remaining contents, but you cannot scroll a `TextView` by default. You can make it scrollable in two ways:

**1. Using `ScrollView`**

ScrollView is a view group that is used to make scrollable views. A scroll view contains a single direct child only.
```
&lt;ScrollView
        android:id=&quot;@+id/SCROLLER_ID&quot;
        android:layout_width=&quot;match_parent&quot;
        android:layout_height=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
        android:scrollbars=&quot;vertical&quot;&gt;

&lt;TextView
        android:id=&quot;@+id/YOUR_TEXT_VIEW&quot;
        android:layout_width=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
        android:layout_height=&quot;wrap_content&quot;/&gt;

&lt;/ScrollView&gt;
```
Note: You can set constraints to the scroll view as you like.

**2. Programmatically**

Set this property to your `TextView` in the layout file.
```
android:scrollbars = &quot;vertical&quot;
```
and then use this code to make it scrollable.
```
yourTextView.setMovementMethod(new ScrollingMovementMethod());
```

